# Tauri's dev watcher is "kill-then-build": it kills the running app on every
# save, then compiles. A broken mid-edit takes the app (and any running
# Claude/Codex sessions) down with it.
#
# So we hide the Rust source from Tauri's watcher. A gated watcher
# (scripts/desktop-dev-green.sh) runs `cargo check` and only touches build.rs
# once the crate compiles cleanly — that touch is what triggers Tauri to
# rebuild + relaunch. Net effect: the app only restarts on a green compile.
#
# Only takes effect when launched via `pnpm desktop:dev:green`. Plain
# `pnpm desktop:dev` ignores this file's intent because nothing touches build.rs.
src/
